                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d405">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">835.00/1653: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-23T23:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 23, 1943—11 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1092. Your 1604, July 19, 6 p.m. The Department thoroughly approves the line of
                    thought you pursue in your conversation with the Minister of Finance regarding
                    the report that our Government is no longer interested in seeing a break of
                    relations by Argentina. The Department’s position remains as set forth in the
                    Under Secretary’s letter to you of June 28.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
